Playground fights by political parties in Tshwane are completely out of control. Gauteng Premier David Makhura has dissolved the municipality and placed it under administration. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC in Tshwane says it can't be held responsible for the chaos in the capital city. Gauteng Premier David Makhura dissolved the municipality following continuous leadership battles. ANC chairperson in Tshwane Dr Kgosi Maepa said the Democratic Alliance was to blame for the lack of service delivery in Tshwane. WATCH: ANC briefing on Tshwane municipality issues “The issues that the DA stopped service delivery here. The ANC can't take responsibility because we were the opposition,” said Maepa. The team leading it will be announced in a week, with new elections expected within 90 days.